porarily closed,<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.scmp.com/news/china/diplomacy/article/3073897/coronavirus-european-borders-likely-remain-open-despite-crisis |title=Coronavirus: European borders likely to remain open despite crisis in Italy, observers say |date=7 March 2020 |work=[[South China Morning Post]] |access-date=15 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200315040544/https://www.scmp.com/news/china/diplomacy/article/3073897/coronavirus-european-borders-likely-remain-open-despite-crisis |archive-date=15 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> the [[European Union]] by 13 March continued to reject the idea of suspending the [[Schengen Area|Schengen free travel area]] and introducing border controls with Italy.<ref name=\"dw-schengen\">{{Cite news |url=https://www.dw.com/en/coronavirus-eu-rules-out-schengen-border-closures-amid-italy-outbreak/a-52497811 |title=Coronavirus: EU rules out Schengen border closures amid Italy outbreak |date=24 February 2020 |publisher=Deutsche Welle |access-date=15 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200313142436/https://www.dw.com/en/coronavirus-eu-rules-out-schengen-border-closures-amid-italy-outbreak/a-52497811 |archive-date=13 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.bloomberg.com/opinion/articles/2020-02-25/salvini-and-le-pen-don-t-have-a-european-coronavirus-cure |title=Salvini and Le Pen Don't Have a Coronavirus Cure |date=25 February 2020 |work=Bloomberg |access-date=15 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200227122244/https://www.bloomberg.com/opinion/articles/2020-02-25/salvini-and-le-pen-don-t-have-a-european-coronavirus-cure |archive-date=27 February 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/europe/coronavirus-europe-open-borders-eu-italy-france-britain-germany-spain-a9362536.html |title=Coronavirus: Europe's open borders threatened by spread of disease |date=28 February 2020 |work=The Independent |access-date=15 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200317173409/https://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/europe/coronavirus-europe-open-borders-eu-italy-france-britain-germany-spain-a9362536.html |archive-date=17 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.euractiv.com/section/justice-home-affairs/news/commission-chief-warns-against-unilateral-virus-travel-bans/ |title=Commission chief warns against unilateral virus travel bans |date=13 March 2020 |work=[[EURACTIV]] |access-date=18 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200318195056/https://www.euractiv.com/section/justice-home-affairs/news/commission-chief-warns-against-unilateral-virus-travel-bans/ |archive-date=18 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> The deputy leader of the Swiss [[Ticino League]], Lorenzo Quadri, by 29 February had criticised the decision: \"It is alarming that the dogma of wide-open borders is considered a priority.\"<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2020/02/26/world/europe/coronavirus-european-union.html |title=Coronavirus Nightmare Could Be the End for Europe's Borderless Dream |date=26 February 2020 |work=The New York Times |access-date=15 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200303055756/https://www.nytimes.com/2020/02/26/world/europe/coronavirus-european-union.html |archive-date=3 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> United States President [[Donald Trump]] said by 12 March the European Union had \"failed to take the same precautions and restrict travel from China and other hot spots\" as the US had implemented.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-health-coronavirus-usa-trump/trump-suspends-all-travel-from-europe-to-the-united-states-to-fight-coronavirus-idUSKBN20Z04U |title=In dramatic step, Trump restricts travel from Europe to US to fight coronavirus |date=12 March 2020 |agency=Reuters |access-date=15 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200314140433/https://www.reuters.com/article/us-health-coronavirus-usa-trump/trump-suspends-all-travel-from-europe-to-the-united-states-to-fight-coronavirus-idUSKBN20Z04U |archive-date=14 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nBy 9 March Czech Prime Minister [[Andrej Babi\u0161]] stated that \"European countries cannot ban the entry of Italian citizens within the Schengen area. The only possible way is to have the Italian prime minister call on his fellow citizens to refrain from traveling to other countries of the European Union.\"<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.schengenvisainfo.com/news/czech-pm-italians-should-be-banned-from-travelling-due-to-coronavirus/ |title=Czech PM: Italians Should Be Banned From Travelling Due to Coronavirus |date=9 March 2020 |work=SchengenVisaInfo.com |access-date=15 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200323171345/https://www.schengenvisainfo.com/news/czech-pm-italians-should-be-banned-from-travelling-due-to-coronavirus/ |archive-date=23 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nAfter Czech Republic, Slovakia, Poland and Denmark announced complete closure of their national borders, the [[European Commission]] President [[Ursula von der Leyen]] said by 12 March that \"Certain controls may be justified, but general travel bans are not seen as being the most effective by the World Health Organization. Moreover, they have a strong social and economic impact, they disrupt people\u2019s lives and business across the borders.\"<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.ft.com/content/4e89ec5c-6565-11ea-b3f3-fe4680ea68b5 |title=Denmark, Poland and Czechs seal borders over coronavirus |date=12 March 2020 |agency=Financial Times |access-date=15 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200314202823/https://www.ft.com/content/4e89ec5c-6565-11ea-b3f3-fe4680ea68b5 |archive-date=14 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> European Union leaders condemned the US decision to restrict travel from Europe to the United States. [[European Council]] President [[Charles Michel]] and Ursula von der Leyen said in a joint statement: \"The European Union disapproves of the fact that the US decision to impose a travel ban was taken unilaterally and without consultation.\"<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://apnews.com/4552fd280d06cf83c63e4cc9b08fe5ce |title=EU condemns Trump travel ban from Europe as virus spreads |date=12 March 2020 |work=Associated Press (AP) |access-date=15 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200313140528/https://apnews.com/4552fd280d06cf83c63e4cc9b08fe5ce |archive-date=13 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> Ursula von der Leyen admitted by 17 March that \"all of us who are not experts initially underestimated the coronavirus.\"<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.euractiv.com/section/coronavirus/news/politicians-underestimated-virus-threat-von-der-leyen-admits/ |title=Politicians 'underestimated' virus threat, von der Leyen admits |date=18 March 2020 |work=Euractiv |access-date=21 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200319152350/https://www.euractiv.com/section/coronavirus/news/politicians-underestimated-virus-threat-von-der-leyen-admits/ |archive-date=19 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nThe Italian government has criticised EU's lack of solidarity with Italy.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://foreignpolicy.com/2020/03/14/coronavirus-eu-abandoning-italy-china-aid/ |title=The EU Is Abandoning Italy in Its Hour of Need |date=14 March 2020 |work=Foreign Policy |access-date=15 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200315112947/https://foreignpolicy.com/2020/03/14/coronavirus-eu-abandoning-italy-china-aid/ |archive-date=15 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2020/mar/11/italy-criticises-eu-being-slow-help-coronavirus-epidemic |title=Italy criticises EU for being slow to help over coronavirus epidemic |date=11 March 2020 |work=The Guardian |access-date=15 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200313000621/https://www.theguardian.com/world/2020/mar/11/italy-criticises-eu-being-slow-help-coronavirus-epidemic |archive-date=13 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.ft.com/content/d3bc25ea-652c-11ea-b3f3-fe4680ea68b5 |title=Italy wonders where Europe's solidarity is as coronavirus strains show |date=13 March 2020 |work=Financial Times |access-date=15 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200315154437/https://www.ft.com/content/d3bc25ea-652c-11ea-b3f3-fe4680ea68b5 |archive-date=15 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=https://news.cgtn.com/news/2020-03-12/Italy-calls-for-extra-help-for-COVID-19-only-China-responded--ONp6w2rmvu/index.html |title=Italy criticizes EU for not responding its call for help, 'only China responded bilaterally' |date=12 March 2020 |work=CGTN |access-date=15 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200316024124/https://news.cgtn.com/news/2020-03-12/Italy-calls-for-extra-help-for-COVID-19-only-China-responded--ONp6w2rmvu/index.html |archive-date=16 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> ''Politico'' reported on 7 March that \"EU countries have so far refused Italy's plea for help fighting coronavirus, as national capitals worry that they may need to stockpile face masks and other medical gear to help their own citizens, officials and diplomats said.\"<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.politico.eu/article/eu-aims-better-control-coronavirus-responses/ |title=Europe fails to help Italy in coronavirus fight |date=7 March 2020 |work=Politico |access-date=15 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200317055659/https://www.politico.eu/article/eu-aims-better-control-coronavirus-responses/ |archive-date=17 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> Maurizio Massari, Italy's ambassador to the EU, said that \"Only China responded bilaterally. Certainly, this is not a good sign of European solidarity.\"<ref name=\"politico-corona\" /> [[Serbia]]n President [[Aleksandar Vu\u010di\u0107]] said that \"European solidarity does not exist. That was a fairy tale.\"<ref name=\"politico-corona\">{{Cite news |url=https://www.politico.eu/article/coronavirus-china-winning-propaganda-war/ |title=China is winning the coronavirus propaganda war |date=18 March 2020 |work=Politico |access-date=21 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200322203919/https://www.politico.eu/article/coronavirus-china-winning-propaganda-war/ |archive-date=22 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nThe planned [[NATO]] \u201c[[List of NATO exercises|Defender 2020]]\u201d military exercise in Germany, Poland, and the Baltic states,<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.spectator.co.uk/article/how-coronavirus-derailed-the-largest-nato-exercise-in-25-years |title=How coronavirus derailed the largest Nato exercise in 25 years |date=20 March 2020 |work=The Spectator |access-date=25 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200325102257/https://www.spectator.co.uk/article/how-coronavirus-derailed-the-largest-nato-exercise-in-25-years |archive-date=25 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> the largest NATO war manoeuvres since the end of the [[Cold War]], was to be held on a reduced scale because of the coronavirus pandemic.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-health-coronavirus-nato/nato-scales-down-exercises-due-to-coronavirus-idUSKBN21627V |title=NATO scales down exercises due to coronavirus |date=19 March 2020 |agency=Reuters |access-date=25 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200325102254/https://www.reuters.com/article/us-health-coronavirus-nato/nato-scales-down-exercises-due-to-coronavirus-idUSKBN21627V |archive-date=25 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> The [[Campaign for Nuclear Disarmament]]'s general secretary [[Kate Hudson (activist)|Kate Hudson]] critisiced the Defender 2020 exercise: \"In the current public-health crisis, it jeopardises the lives not only of the troops from the US and the many European countries participating but the inhabitants of the countries in which they are operating.\"<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://morningstaronline.co.uk/article/b/nato-must-end-dangerous-and-irresponsible-military-exercise-on-russias-border-campaigners-say |title=Nato must end 'dangerous and irresponsible' military exercise on Russia's border, campaigners say |date=18 March 2020 |work=Morning Star |access-date=25 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200320010441/https://morningstaronline.co.uk/article/b/nato-must-end-dangerous-and-irresponsible-military-exercise-on-russias-border-campaigners-say |archive-date=20 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n* [[PREPARE]] (EU PREPARE project)\n* [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic by country and territory]]\n\n==Notes==\n{{Reflist|group=nb}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* [https://corona.arrangy.com Worldwide Coronavirus Map, confirmed Cases] \u2013 Map the route paths of coronavirus confirmed cases.\n* [https://systems.jhu.edu/research/public-health/ncov/ ncov \u2013 CSSE] - Map of the expansion of the virus in Europe and in the world\n{{COVID-19}}\n\n[[Category:2020 in Europe|coronavirus pandemic]]\n[[Category:Health disasters in Europe]]\n[[Category:2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic by continent|Europe]]\n[[Category:2020 coronavirus pandemic in Europe| ]]\n", "name_user": "Natanieluz", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eStatistics by country", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2020_coronavirus_pandemic_in_Europe"}
{"title_page": "AZS AJP Gorz\u00f3w Wielkopolski", "text_new": "{{Infobox Basketball club\n| color1        = #FFFFFF\n| color2        = #000080\n| color3        = #007FFF\n| name          = AZS AJP Gorz\u00f3w Wielkopolski\n| nickname      = ''Akademiczki''\n| logo          =\n| imagesize     = \n| league        = [[Basket Liga Kobiet]]<br>[[EuroCup Women]]\n| founded       = {{Start date and age|2001}}\n| history       = '''AZS PWSZ Gorz\u00f3w Wielkopolski'''<br>2001\u20132015<br>'''AZS AJP Gorz\u00f3w Wielkopolski'''<br>2016\u2013present\n| arena         = Hala AJP\n| capacity      = 1,000\n| location      = [[Gorz\u00f3w Wielkopolski]], [[Poland]]\n| colors        = Navy, azure, white<ref>{{cite web|title=Barwy klubu|url=http://azsajpgorzow.pl/klub/social|publisher=azsajpgorzow.pl|accessdate=19 December 2018|language=pl}}</ref><br>{{color box|navy}} {{color box|#007FFF}} {{color box|white}}\n| president     = Krzysztof Kielec\n| coach         = Dariusz Maciejewski\n| championships = \n| website       = [http://www.azsajpgorzow.pl/ azsajpgorzow.pl]\n| 1_title       = Home\n| 1_body        = FFFFFF\n| 1_pattern_b   = _navyshoulders\n| 1_shorts      = FFFFFF\n| 1_pattern_s   = _navysides\n| 2_title       = Away\n| 2_body        = 000080\n| 2_pattern_b   = _whiteshoulders\n| 2_shorts      = 000080\n| 2_pattern_s   = _whitesides\n}}\n\n'''AZS AJP Gorz\u00f3w Wielkopolski''' is a [[Poland|polish]] professional women's [[basketball]] club that was founded in 2001 in the city of [[Gorz\u00f3w Wielkopolski]]. AZS AJP Gorz\u00f3w Wielkopolski plays in the [[Basket Liga Kobiet]], the highest competition in [[Poland]]<ref>{{cite web|title=Team|url=https://basketball.eurobasket.com/team/Poland/InvestInTheWest-AZS-AJP-Gorzow-Wlkp/7594?Women=1|publisher=basketball.eurobasket.com|accessdate=9 December 2018|language=pl}}</ref>. In the 2019-20 season the team is also playing in [[EuroCup Women]]<ref>{{cite web|title=EuroCup Women 2019\u201320 teams|url=http://www.fiba.basketball/eurocupwomen/19-20/team/Gorzow#tab=roster|publisher=fiba.basketball|accessdate=14 March 2020|language=en}}</ref>.\n\n==History==\n{{Empty section|date=February 2019}}\n\n==Honours==\n===Domestic===\n*'''[[Basket Liga Kobiet|Polish League]]'''<ref>{{cite web|title=Statystyki dru\u017cyny w poszczeg\u00f3lnych sezonach|url=http://www.plkhistory.ugu.pl/plkk/index.php?druzyny&id=16&ids=&wyniki|publisher=plkhistory.ugu.pl|accessdate=9 December 2018|language=pl}}</ref>\n:Runner-up (3): 2008\u201309, 2009\u201310, 2018\u201319\n:Bronze (3): 2007\u201308, 2010\u201311, 2019\u201320\n\n===European===\n*'''[[EuroCup Women|EuroCup]]'''<ref>{{cite web|title=History EuroCup Women|url=http://www.fiba.basketball/eurocupwomen/18-19/history|publisher=fiba.basketball|accessdate=16 December 2018|language=en}}</ref>\n:Round of 16 (2): 2007\u201308, [[2018\u201319 EuroCup Women|2018-19]]\n\n==Season by season==\n{|class=\"wikitable\" style=\"font-size:85%\"\n!Season\n![[Polish basketball league system|Tier]]\n!League\n!{{Tooltip|Pos.|Position after playoffs}}\n!colspan=2| European competitions\n|-\n|style=\"background:#efefef;\"|2001\u201302\n| align=\"center\"|2\n| I Liga\n| align=\"center\"|5th\n| colspan=2|\n|-\n|style=\"background:#efefef;\"|2002\u201303\n| align=\"center\"|2\n| I Liga\n| align=\"center\"|5th\n| colspan=2|\n|-\n|style=\"background:#efefef;\"|2003\u201304\n| align=\"center\"|2\n| I Liga\n| style=\"background:#BBF3BB\" align=\"center\"|1st\n| colspan=2|\n|-\n|style=\"background:#efefef;\"|2004\u201305\n| align=\"center\"|1\n| [[Basket Liga Kobiet|BLK]]\n| align=\"center\"|8th\n| colspan=2|\n|-\n|style=\"background:#efefef;\"|2005\u201306\n| align=\"center\"|1\n| [[Basket Liga Kobiet|BLK]]\n| align=\"center\"|5th\n| colspan=2|\n|-\n|style=\"background:#efefef;\"|2006\u201307\n| align=\"center\"|1\n| [[Basket Liga Kobiet|BLK]]\n| align=\"center\"|4th\n| colspan=2|\n|-\n|style=\"background:#efefef;\"|2007\u201308\n| align=\"center\"|1\n| [[Basket Liga Kobiet|BLK]]\n| sty