sty_20190621_policeviolence\">{{cite web|url=https://www.amnesty.org.hk/en/verified-hong-kong-police-violence-against-peaceful-protesters/|title=Verified: Hong Kong Police Violence Against Peaceful Protesters|publisher=[[Amnesty International]]|date=21 June 2019|accessdate=20 August 2019}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"amnesty_20190901_policeprotest\">{{cite web |title=Hong Kong: Rampaging police must be investigated |url=https://www.amnesty.org/en/latest/news/2019/09/hong-kong-rampaging-police-protest/ |publisher=Amnesty International |accessdate=1 September 2019 |date=1 September 2019 |quote=In response to the latest clashes between police and protesters in Hong Kong on Saturday night \u2013 including one incident where police stormed the platform of Prince Edward metro station and beat people on a train \u2013 Man-Kei Tam, Director of Amnesty International Hong Kong, said: \"Violence directed at police on Saturday is no excuse for officers to go on the rampage elsewhere. The horrifying scenes at Prince Edward metro station, which saw terrified bystanders caught up in the melee, fell far short of international policing standards.}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"ap_20190824_36arrested\">{{cite web |last1=Chan |first1=Kelvin |last2=Cheung |first2=Kin |title=Hong Kong police draw guns, arrest 36 from latest protest |url=https://apnews.com/b116e37159164abb9bfede0bc341dd0a |agency=[[Associated Press]] |accessdate=31 August 2019 |date=24 August 2019}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"ap_20191105_knifearrest\">{{cite news |last1=Ng |first1=Eileen |title=Hong Kong police arrest man in knife attack at protest site |url=https://apnews.com/fea5339c6b414b82a7df89331e5800ee |accessdate=5 November 2019 |agency=[[Associated Press]] |date=5 November 2019}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"appledaily_20736871\">{{cite web|url=https://hk.news.appledaily.com/local/daily/article/20190725/20736871 |script-title=zh:\u5143\u6717\u6050\u8972 ICAC\u67e5\u8b66\u9ed1\u52fe\u7d50 \u524d\u8abf\u67e5\u54e1\uff1a\u5018\u8896\u624b\u65c