{"title_page": "Clap for our Carers", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date = April 2020}}\n{{Use British English|date=April 2020}}\n{{Infobox recurring event\n|name              = <!--Uses page name if omitted-->\n|native_name       = \n|native_name_lang  = \n|logo              = Clap_for_our_Carers_Logo.jpg\n|logo_alt          = Cartoon hands clapping with the text #clapforourcarers\n|logo_caption      = \n|logo_size         = \n|image             = \n|image_size        = \n|alt               = \n|caption           = \n|status            = Active\n|genre             = Social media organised event\n|date              = <!-- {{start date|YYYY|mm|dd}} \"dates=\" also works, but do not use both -->\n|begins            = 26 March 2020\n|ends              = <!-- {{end date|YYYY|mm|dd}} -->\n|frequency         = Weekly (8 pm Thursdays)\n|venue             = \n|location          = [[United Kingdom]]\n|coordinates       = <!-- {{coord|LAT|LON|type:event|display=inline,title}} --> \n|country           = \n|years_active      = <!-- {{age|YYYY|mm|dd}} Date of the first occurrence -->\n|first             = {{start date|2020|March|26|20|00|GMT|df=yes}} <!-- First Clap for our Carers was before BST-->\n|founder_name      = <!-- or | founders = -->\n|last              = <!-- Date of most recent event; if the event will not be held again, use {{End date|YYYY|MM|DD|df=y}} -->\n|prev              = \n|next              = \n|participants      = UK residents\n|attendance        = \n|capacity          = \n|area              = \n|budget            = \n|activity          = \n|leader_name       = \n|patron            = \n|organised         = Annemarie Plas\n|filing            = \n|people            = [[Boris Johnson]]<br>[[Rishi Sunak]]\n|member            = \n|sponsor           = <!-- | or sponsors = -->\n|website           = {{url|https://clapforourcarers.co.uk/}}\n|current           = \n|footnotes         = \n}}\n'''Clap for our Carers''', also known as '''Clap for the NHS''' or '''Clap for Key Workers''' is a recurring gesture of appreciation for the workers of Britain's [[National Health Service]] (NHS) and other [[key worker]]s during the [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic|global pandemic]] of [[severe acute respiratory syndrome coronavirus 2]] (SARS-CoV-2), which causes [[coronavirus disease 2019]] (COVID-19),  and spread to the [[United Kingdom]] in January 2020.\n\nThe idea came from Annemarie Plas and the first event took place on Thursday 26 March 2020 at 8 pm. The following week Plas posted on [[instagram]] \u201ctonight we will show our appreciation again! For ALL that go out to work so that we can stay in!\u201d.<ref name=\"Barr\"/> Several celebrities have supported the campaign.\n\ncomplete bollocks\n\n==Origins==\nThe idea for the event came from Annemarie Plas, a Dutch Londoner, who had seen a similar event in the Netherlands.<ref name=Telegraph>{{cite news| url= https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/0/clap-carers-time-nhs-applause-tonight/| title= Clap For Our Carers: what time is the NHS applause tonight?| last=Penna| first=Dominic| work=[[The Daily Telegraph]]| date=2 April 2020| accessdate=7 April 2020}}</ref> Similar activities occurred in Italy, Spain and the Netherlands in the weeks prior to the event.<ref name=Telegraph/><ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/av/world-europe-51895386/coronavirus-spain-and-italy-applaud-health-workers |title=Coronavirus: Spain and Italy applaud health workers |date=15 March 2020 |work=BBC News |access-date=2020-03-02 |language=en-GB }}</ref>\n\n==Description==\nOn Thursday 26 March 2020 at 8 pm, people across the UK clapped, cheered, and rang bells to thank NHS workers for their role in during the pandemic.<ref name=COVIDTimeline>{{Cite web|url=https://bfpg.co.uk/2020/03/covid-19-timeline/|title=COVID-19 Timeline|last=Holmes|first=Flora|date=2020-03-27|website=British Foreign Policy Group|language=en-GB|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=8 April 2020}}</ref> [[Prince George of Cambridge|Princes George]] and [[Prince Louis of Cambridge|Louis]], and [[Princess Charlotte of Cambridge|Princess Charlotte]] also supported the event from their residence at [[Anmer Hall]].<ref name=Telegraph/><ref>{{cite news| url= https://www.independent.co.uk/life-style/royal-family/clap-for-our-carers-prince-george-charlotte-louis-royal-family-nhs-coronavirus-a9429411.html| title= CLAP FOR OUR CARERS: HARRY AND MEGHAN JOIN PRINCE GEORGE, CHARLOTTE AND LOUIS IN APPLAUSE FOR NHS WORKERS| work=[[The Independent]]| date=27 March 2020| accessdate=7 April 2020}}</ref>\n\nThe event is typically a round of applause outside a participating person's home or from one of their windows, however people have also taken part by banging pots and pans, playing music and setting off fireworks. Millions are reported to have taken part.<ref name=Bowman>{{Cite news |last=Bowman |first=Verity |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2020/03/26/thank-nhs-tonights-clap-carers/ |title=Clap For Our Carers: How thousands of Britons thanked the NHS with a national round of applause |date=26 March 2020 |work=The Telegraph|access-date=2020-03-26 |language=en-GB |issn=0307-1235}}</ref> \n\nA week later, Plas posted on [[instagram]] \u201ctonight we will show our appreciation again! For ALL that go out to work so that we can stay in!\u201d.<ref name=\"Barr\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/life-style/health-and-families/coronavirus-nhs-workers-applause-clap-for-our-carers-when-time-covid-19-a9426906.html|title=How to join in with tonight's national 'Clap For Our Carers' event for NHS and key workers|last=|first=|date=5 April 2020|website=The Independent|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=8 April 2020}}</ref> The campaign was subsequently repeated on 2 April, receiving widespread media attention, including by the state-funded broadcaster, the [[BBC]].<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/live/world-52130552 |title=Coronavirus: Applause for key workers rings out across the UK |date=2 April 2020 |work=BBC News |access-date=2020-03-02 |language=en-GB }}</ref> On that day, [[Windsor Castle]], where [[Elizabeth II|The Queen]] and [[Prince Philip, Duke of Edinburgh|Prince Philip]] are [[self-isolating]], was turned blue for the Clap for our Carers event.<ref>{{cite news| url= https://www.standard.co.uk/insider/royalssociety/queen-elizabeth-clap-for-our-carers-selfisolation-windsor-castle-a4406026.html| title= Queen Elizabeth makes grand Clap For Our Carers gesture from self-isolation in Windsor Castle| last=Hills| first=Megan| work=[[Evening Standard]]| date=4 April 2020| accessdate=7 April 2020}}</ref> Several notable buildings were also lit up in blue during the events. These have included [[The Shard]], [[Tower Bridge]], the [[London Eye]], and [[MediaCityUK]].<ref>{{cite news| url= https://www.standard.co.uk/news/uk/clap-for-our-carers-nhs-mass-applause-coronavirus-a4404706.html| title= Clap for our Carers returns tonight after calls for Brits to repeat mass applause for NHS coronavirus heroes| work=[[Evening Standard]]| date=3 April 2020| accessdate=7 April 2020}}</ref> \n\nThe event is expected to take place every Thursday during the [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in the United Kingdom|coronavirus pandemic]].<ref name=Telegraph/> In each week, major political and social figures have supported the event, including the [[Prime Minister of the United Kingdom|Prime Minister]] [[Boris Johnson]] who clapped outside [[10 Downing Street]] with [[Rishi Sunak]], the [[Chancellor of the Exchequer]].<ref name=\":0\" />\n\n==Response==\n[[File:NW-ThankYouCollage.jpg|thumb|''Thank You'' collage by [[Nathan Wyburn]], 2020.]]\nClap for our Carers inspired [[Nathan Wyburn]] to produce a collage made of more than 200 images of NHS workers.<ref> {{Cite web|url=https://www.penarthtimes.co.uk/news/18352935.artist-pays-special-tribute-front-line-nhs-workers/|title=Artist pays special tribute to front-line NHS workers|last=Draper|first=Joseph|date=2 April 2020|website=Penarth Times|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=7 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Related==\nAfter Prime Minister Boris Johnson was taken to hospital, people suggested a Clap for Boris, in the same vein at Clap for our Carers. The Clap for Boris is scheduled for 7 April.<ref>{{cite news| url= https://www.indy100.com/article/boris-johnson-coronavirus-hospital-intensive-care-clap-nhs-9451681| title= With Boris Johnson in intensive care, there's a campaign to make a national #ClapForBoris happen and people are divided about it| work=[[The Independent]]| date=7 April 2020| accessdate=7 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist|colwidth=30em}}\n\n{{2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic}}\n{{2020 coronavirus pandemic in the United Kingdom}}\n{{Portal bar|United Kingdom|Medicine|Viruses}}\n\n[[Category:2020 coronavirus pandemic in the United Kingdom]]\n[[Category:March 2020 events in the United Kingdom]]\n[[Category:April 2020 events in the United Kingdom]]\n[[Category:Reactions to 2020s events]]\n[[Category:National responses to the 2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date = April 2020}}\n{{Use British English|date=April 2020}}\n{{Infobox recurring event\n|name              = <!--Uses page name if omitted-->\n|native_name       = \n|native_name_lang  = \n|logo              = Clap_for_our_Carers_Logo.jpg\n|logo_alt          = Cartoon hands clapping with the text #clapforourcarers\n|logo_caption      = \n|logo_size         = \n|image             = \n|image_size        = \n|alt               = \n|caption           = \n|status            = Active\n|genre             = Social media organised event\n|date              = <!-- {{start date|YYYY|mm|dd}} \"dates=\" also works, but do not use both -->\n|begins            = 26 March 2020\n|ends              = <!-- {{end date|YYYY|mm|dd}} -->\n|frequency         = Weekly (8 pm Thursdays)\n|venue             = \n|location          = [[United Kingdom]]\n|coordinates       = <!-- {{coord|LAT|LON|type:event|display=inline,title}} --> \n|country           = \n|years_active      = <!-- {{age|YYYY|mm|dd}} Date of the first occurrence -->\n|first             = {{start date|2020|March|26|20|00|GMT|df=yes}} <!-- First Clap for our Carers was before BST-->\n|founder_name      = <!-- or | founders = -->\n|last              = <!-- Date of most recent event; if the event will not be held again, use {{End date|YYYY|MM|DD|df=y}} -->\n|prev              = \n|next              = \n|participants      = UK residents\n|attendance        = \n|capacity          = \n|area              = \n|budget            = \n|activity          = \n|leader_name       = \n|patron            = \n|organised         = Annemarie Plas\n|filing            = \n|people            = [[Boris Johnson]]<br>[[Rishi Sunak]]\n|member            = \n|sponsor           = <!-- | or sponsors = -->\n|website           = {{url|https://clapforourcarers.co.uk/}}\n|current           = \n|footnotes         = \n}}\n'''Clap for our Carers''', also known as '''Clap for the NHS''' or '''Clap for Key Workers''' is a recurring gesture of appreciation for the workers of Britain's [[National Health Service]] (NHS) and other [[key worker]]s during the [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic|global pandemic]] of [[severe acute respiratory syndrome coronavirus 2]] (SARS-CoV-2), which causes [[coronavirus disease 2019]] (COVID-19),  and spread to the [[United Kingdom]] in January 2020.\n\nThe idea came from Annemarie Plas and the first event took place on Thursday 26 March 2020 at 8 pm. The following week Plas posted on [[instagram]] \u201ctonight we will show our appreciation again! For ALL that go out to work so that we can stay in!\u201d.<ref name=\"Barr\"/> Several celebrities have supported the campaign.\n\n==Origins==\nThe idea for the event came from Annemarie Plas, a Dutch Londoner, who had seen a similar event in the Netherlands.<ref name=Telegraph>{{cite news| url= https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/0/clap-carers-time-nhs-applause-tonight/| title= Clap For Our Carers: what time is the NHS applause tonight?| last=Penna| first=Dominic| work=[[The Daily Telegraph]]| date=2 April 2020| accessdate=7 April 2020}}</ref> Similar activities occurred in Italy, Spain and the Netherlands in the weeks prior to the event.<ref name=Telegraph/><ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/av/world-europe-51895386/coronavirus-spain-and-italy-applaud-health-workers |title=Coronavirus: Spain and Italy applaud health workers |date=15 March 2020 |work=BBC News |access-date=2020-03-02 |language=en-GB }}</ref>\n\n==Description==\nOn Thursday 26 March 2020 at 8 pm, people across the UK clapped, cheered, and rang bells to thank NHS workers for their role in during the pandemic.<ref name=COVIDTimeline>{{Cite web|url=https://bfpg.co.uk/2020/03/covid-19-timeline/|title=COVID-19 Timeline|last=Holmes|first=Flora|date=2020-03-27|website=British Foreign Policy Group|language=en-GB|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=8 April 2020}}</ref> [[Prince George of Cambridge|Princes George]] and [[Prince Louis of Cambridge|Louis]], and [[Princess Charlotte of Cambridge|Princess Charlotte]] also supported the event from their residence at [[Anmer Hall]].<ref name=Telegraph/><ref>{{cite news| url= https://www.independent.co.uk/life-style/royal-family/clap-for-our-carers-prince-george-charlotte-louis-royal-family-nhs-coronavirus-a9429411.html| title= CLAP FOR OUR CARERS: HARRY AND MEGHAN JOIN PRINCE GEORGE, CHARLOTTE AND LOUIS IN APPLAUSE FOR NHS WORKERS| work=[[The Independent]]| date=27 March 2020| accessdate=7 April 2020}}</ref>\n\nThe event is typically a round of applause outside a participating person's home or from one of their windows, however people have also taken part by banging pots and pans, playing music and setting off fireworks. Millions are reported to have taken part.<ref name=Bowman>{{Cite news |last=Bowman |first=Verity |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2020/03/26/thank-nhs-tonights-clap-carers/ |title=Clap For Our Carers: How thousands of Britons thanked the NHS with a national round of applause |date=26 March 2020 |work=The Telegraph|access-date=2020-03-26 |language=en-GB |issn=0307-1235}}</ref> \n\nA week later, Plas posted on [[instagram]] \u201ctonight we will show our appreciation again! For ALL that go out to work so that we can stay in!\u201d.<ref name=\"Barr\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/life-style/health-and-families/coronavirus-nhs-workers-applause-clap-for-our-carers-when-time-covid-19-a9426906.html|title=How to join in with tonight's national 'Clap For Our Carers' event for NHS and key workers|last=|first=|date=5 April 2020|website=The Independent|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=8 April 2020}}</ref> The campaign was subsequently repeated on 2 April, receiving widespread media attention, including by the state-funded broadcaster, the [[BBC]].<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/live/world-52130552 |title=Coronavirus: Applause for key workers rings out across the UK |date=2 April 2020 |work=BBC News |access-date=2020-03-02 |language=en-GB }}</ref> On that day, [[Windsor Castle]], where [[Elizabeth II|The Queen]] and [[Prince Philip, Duke of Edinburgh|Prince Philip]] are [[self-isolating]], was turned blue for the Clap for our Carers event.<ref>{{cite news| url= https://www.standard.co.uk/insider/royalssociety/queen-elizabeth-clap-for-our-carers-selfisolation-windsor-castle-a4406026.html| title= Queen Elizabeth makes grand Clap For Our Carers gesture from self-isolation in Windsor Castle| last=Hills| first=Megan| work=[[Evening Standard]]| date=4 April 2020| accessdate=7 April 2020}}</ref> Several notable buildings were also lit up in blue during the events. These have included [[The Shard]], [[Tower Bridge]], the [[London Eye]], and [[MediaCityUK]].<ref>{{cite news| url= https://www.standard.co.uk/news/uk/clap-for-our-carers-nhs-mass-applause-coronavirus-a4404706.html| title= Clap for our Carers returns tonight after calls for Brits to repeat mass applause for NHS coronavirus heroes| work=[[Evening Standard]]| date=3 April 2020| accessdate=7 April 2020}}</ref> \n\nThe event is expected to take place every Thursday during the [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in the United Kingdom|coronavirus pandemic]].<ref name=Telegraph/> In each week, major political and social figures have supported the event, including the [[Prime Minister of the United Kingdom|Prime Minister]] [[Boris Johnson]] who clapped outside [[10 Downing Street]] with [[Rishi Sunak]], the [[Chancellor of the Exchequer]].<ref name=\":0\" />\n\n==Response==\n[[File:NW-ThankYouCollage.jpg|thumb|''Thank You'' collage by [[Nathan Wyburn]], 2020.]]\nClap for our Carers inspired [[Nathan Wyburn]] to produce a collage made of more than 200 images of NHS workers.<ref> {{Cite web|url=https://www.penarthtimes.co.uk/news/18352935.artist-pays-special-tribute-front-line-nhs-workers/|title=Artist pays special tribute to front-line NHS workers|last=Draper|first=Joseph|date=2 April 2020|website=Penarth Times|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=7 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Related==\nAfter Prime Minister Boris Johnson was taken to hospital, people suggested a Clap for Boris, in the same vein at Clap for our Carers. The Clap for Boris is scheduled for 7 April.<ref>{{cite news| url= https://www.indy100.com/article/boris-johnson-coronavirus-hospital-intensive-care-clap-nhs-9451681| title= With Boris Johnson in intensive care, there's a campaign to make a national #ClapForBoris happen and people are divided about it| work=[[The Independent]]| date=7 April 2020| accessdate=7 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist|colwidth=30em}}\n\n{{2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic}}\n{{2020 coronavirus pandemic in the United Kingdom}}\n{{Portal bar|United Kingdom|Medicine|Viruses}}\n