   = [[Futsal at the Asian Indoor and Martial Arts Games|Asian Indoor and Martial Arts Games]]\n|  2ndRegional cup apps = 3\n|  2ndRegional cup first = [[Futsal at the 2009 Asian Indoor Games|2009]]\n|  2ndRegional cup best = 4th Place, ([[Futsal at the 2009 Asian Indoor Games|2009]])\n|  Grand Prix apps    = \n|  Grand Prix first   = \n|  Grand Prix best    = \n|  Confederations cup apps  = \n|  Confederations cup first = \n|  Confederations cup best  = \n}}\n\nThe '''Turkmenistan national futsal team''' represents [[Turkmenistan]] in international [[futsal]] competitions and is controlled by the [[Football Federation of Turkmenistan]].\n\n==Overview==\nTurkmenistan can count themselves fortunate to have avoided preliminary qualification for the [[2008 AFC Futsal Championship]]. They grabbed the last direct spot in the finals even though they finished bottom of their finals group in 2007. Turkmenistan caused the first real upset of the championship with a 1-0 win over Australia in their opening game, Elman Tagayev scoring the only goal in the first half. But they went backwards after that with a 1-7 loss to Kyrgyzstan and a 2-5 reversal to Korea Republic. Turkmenistan were not expected to make it out of the group after poor performances in previous championships. They were uninspiring in 2005 and the following year had little chance in a group that included powerhouses Iran and ASEAN kingpins Thailand. But with more games under their belt, the relatively young squad will be aiming for better results this year.\n\nIn March 2019, the [[Football Federation of Turkmenistan]] named [[Robert Grdovi\u0107]] as the head coach of the Turkmenistan national futsal team, signing a one year contract<ref>[https://turkmenportal.com/blog/18042/horvatskii-specialist-rober-grdovich-vozglavit-nacionalnuyu-sbornuyu-turkmenistana-po-futzalu \u0425\u043e\u0440\u0432\u0430\u0442\u0441\u043a\u0438\u0439 \u0441\u043f\u0435\u0446\u0438\u0430\u043b\u0438\u0441\u0442 \u0420\u043e\u0431\u0435\u0440\u0442 \u0413\u0440\u0434\u043e\u0432\u0438\u0447 \u0432\u043e\u0437\u0433\u043b\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0442 \u043d\u0430\u0446\u0438\u043e\u043d\u0430\u043b\u044c\u043d\u0443\u044e \u0441\u0431\u043e\u0440\u043d\u0443\u044e \u0422\u0443\u0440\u043a\u043c\u0435\u043d\u0438\u0441\u0442\u0430\u043d\u0430 \u043f\u043e \u0444\u0443\u0442\u0437\u0430\u043b\u0443]</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://futsalfeed.com/original-content/robert-grdovic-talks-about-postponed-afc-futsal-championship-and-predicts-the-outcome|title=Robert Grdovic talks about postponed AFC Futsal Championship and predicts the outcome|publisher=futsallfeed.com| accessdate=2020-04-08}}</ref>.\n\n==Tournament records==\n\n===FIFA Futsal World Cup===\n* [[1989 FIFA Futsal World Championship|1989]] \u2013 ''Part of Soviet Union''\n* [[1992 FIFA Futsal World Championship|1992]] \u2013 ''Did not enter''\n* [[1996 FIFA Futsal World Championship|1996]] \u2013 ''Did not enter''\n* [[2000 FIFA Futsal World Championship|2000]] \u2013 ''Did not enter''\n* [[2004 FIFA Futsal World Championship|2004]] \u2013 ''Did not enter''\n* [[2008 FIFA Futsal World Cup|2008]] \u2013 ''Did not qualify''\n* [[2012 FIFA Futsal World Cup|2012]] \u2013 ''Did not qualify''\n* [[2016 FIFA Futsal World Cup|2016]] \u2013 ''Did not qualify''\n* [[2020 FIFA Futsal World Cup|2020]] \u2013 ''TBD''\n\n===[[AFC Futsal Championship]]===\n{{see also|AFC Futsal Championship}}\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align: center;font-size:90%;\"\n!colspan=10|[[AFC Futsal Championship|Asian Championship record]]\n|-\n!width=125|Year\n!width=150|Round\n!width=35|Pld\n!width=35|W\n!width=35|D\n!width=35|L\n!width=35|GS\n!width=35|GA\n!width=35|DIF\n!width=35|Points\n|-\n|{{flagicon|MAS}}  [[1999 AFC Futsal Championship|1999]]||rowspan=3 colspan=9|''Did Not Enter''\n|-\n|{{flagicon|THA}} [[2000 AFC Futsal Championship|2000]]\n|-\n|{{flagicon|IRI}} [[2001 AFC Futsal Championship|2001]]\n|-\n|{{flagicon|IDN}} [[2002 AFC Futsal Championship|2002]]||rowspan